name: Bab Oqla - Oqla Gate
address: Bab Oqla, Medina of Tetouan, Tetouan 93000, Morocco
description: Historic gate of the Medina of Tetouan, also known as Bab al-Aqla or the Gate of Ugliness. Built during the Moroccan period, this monumental gate represents the traditional Moroccan Islamic architectural style with intricate zellige tilework and carved cedar doors. The gate features a defensive structure typical of medieval Moroccan fortifications and serves as one of the main entrances to the UNESCO World Heritage-listed Medina of Tetouan. The structure showcases traditional craftsmanship with ornamental arches and historical significance as a cultural landmark.
